1. git branch — list local branches.

2. git branch <filename> — create a new branch.

3. git switch <filename> (or git checkout feature-readme) — switch to that branch.

4. git switch -c <filename> — create and switch in one step.

5. git merge <filename> — merge the feature branch into your current branch.

6. git branch -d <filename> — delete a merged branch.

7. git pull — fetch and merge the latest changes from the remote repository.
